1 Introduction
**************

T-Lisp (tmax Lisp) is a Lisp-1 dialect embedded in the tmax terminal
text editor.  It provides all editor extensibility through a
comprehensive API.

   • *Lisp-1 dialect* -- variables and functions share the same
     namespace
   • *Lexical scoping* -- variables are scoped to their defining block
   • *Tail-call optimization* -- recursive calls in tail position use
     constant stack
   • *Macro system* -- full quasiquote support for metaprogramming
   • *200+ editor API functions* -- complete control over the editor
   • *Testing framework* -- built-in test definitions and assertions


