2 Lexical Structure
*******************

2.1 Comments
============

Comments begin with ‘;’ and extend to end of line:

     ;; This is a comment
     (+ 1 2) ; inline comment

2.2 Identifiers
===============

Identifiers may contain letters, digits, and: ‘-’, ‘_’, ‘?’, ‘!’, ‘+’,
‘*’, ‘/’, ‘<’, ‘>’, ‘=’

     x  my-variable  buffer-insert  nil?  set!  +  <=

2.3 String Literals
===================

Double-quoted with escape sequences:

     "hello world"
     "Line 1\nLine 2"
     "Say \"hello\""

2.4 Number Literals
===================

     42    -17    3.14    -2.5

2.5 Special Tokens
==================

‘( )’
     Parentheses delimit lists and function calls
‘'’
     Quote -- shorthand for ‘(quote ...)’
‘`’
     Quasiquote -- template quotation
‘,’
     Unquote -- evaluate within quasiquote
‘,@’
     Unquote-splice -- splice list elements within quasiquote


