7 Standard Library
******************

7.1 Arithmetic
==============

 -- Function: + numbers...
     Addition.  With no arguments returns 0.
          (+)          ; => 0
          (+ 5)        ; => 5
          (+ 1 2 3)    ; => 6

 -- Function: - numbers...
     Subtraction.  With one argument, negation.
          (- 5)        ; => -5
          (- 10 3)     ; => 7
          (- 20 5 2)   ; => 13

 -- Function: * numbers...
     Multiplication.  With no arguments returns 1.
          (*)          ; => 1
          (* 3 4)      ; => 12

 -- Function: / numbers...
     Division.  With one argument, reciprocal.
          (/ 2)        ; => 0.5
          (/ 10 2)     ; => 5

 -- Function: mod dividend divisor
     Modulo operation.
          (mod 7 3)    ; => 1

 -- Function: abs number
     Absolute value.
          (abs -5)     ; => 5

 -- Function: min numbers...
     Minimum of arguments.
          (min 3 1 4 1 5)  ; => 1

 -- Function: max numbers...
     Maximum of arguments.
          (max 3 1 4 1 5)  ; => 5

 -- Function: sqrt number
     Square root.
          (sqrt 16)    ; => 4

 -- Function: expt base exponent
     Exponentiation.
          (expt 2 10)  ; => 1024

 -- Function: floor number
     Round down to integer.

 -- Function: ceiling number
     Round up to integer.

 -- Function: round number
     Round to nearest integer.

 -- Function: ceil number
     Standalone compatibility alias for ‘ceiling’.

 -- Function: pow base exponent
     Standalone compatibility alias for ‘expt’.

7.2 Comparison
==============

 -- Function: = a b
     Numeric equality.
          (= 3 3)      ; => #t
          (= 1 2)      ; => #f

 -- Function: < a b
     Less than.
          (< 1 2)      ; => #t

 -- Function: > a b
     Greater than.
          (> 3 2)      ; => #t

 -- Function: eq a b
     Object identity comparison.

7.3 List Operations
===================

 -- Function: cons elem list
     Prepend ELEM to LIST.
          (cons 1 '(2 3))  ; => (1 2 3)

 -- Function: car list
     First element of LIST.
          (car '(1 2 3))   ; => 1

 -- Function: cdr list
     Rest of LIST after first element.
          (cdr '(1 2 3))   ; => (2 3)

 -- Function: list elements...
     Create a list from arguments.
          (list 1 2 3)     ; => (1 2 3)

 -- Function: append lists...
     Concatenate lists.
          (append '(1 2) '(3 4))  ; => (1 2 3 4)

 -- Function: reverse list
     Reverse a list.
          (reverse '(1 2 3))  ; => (3 2 1)

 -- Function: nth n list
     Get Nth element (0-indexed).
          (nth 0 '(a b c))  ; => a

 -- Function: last list
     Get last element.
          (last '(1 2 3))   ; => 3

 -- Function: member item list
     Find ITEM in LIST; return tail from match or nil.

 -- Function: length string-or-list
     Length of string or list.
          (length "hello")  ; => 5
          (length '(1 2 3)) ; => 3

 -- Function: list-slice list start end
     Return the portion of LIST from START up to but not including END.

 -- Function: mapcar function list
     Apply FUNCTION to each element of LIST and return the result list.

 -- Function: filter predicate list
     Return elements of LIST for which PREDICATE is truthy.

 -- Function: stable-sort predicate list
     Return a sorted copy of LIST.  PREDICATE receives two values and
     should return true when the first should sort before the second.

7.4 String Operations
=====================

 -- Function: substring str start end
     Extract substring from START to END.
          (substring "hello" 1 4)  ; => "ell"

 -- Function: string-append strings...
     Concatenate strings.
          (string-append "hello" " " "world")  ; => "hello world"

 -- Function: string= a b
     String equality.

 -- Function: string< a b
     String less-than (lexicographic).

 -- Function: string> a b
     String greater-than (lexicographic).

 -- Function: string-upcase str
     Convert to uppercase.

 -- Function: string-downcase str
     Convert to lowercase.

 -- Function: string-split str separator
     Split STR by SEPARATOR and return a list of strings.

 -- Function: string-join separator list
     Join LIST with SEPARATOR.  Non-string values are converted with the
     normal T-Lisp printer.

 -- Function: string-trim str
     Trim leading and trailing whitespace.

 -- Function: string-replace str search replacement
     Replace every literal SEARCH occurrence in STR.

 -- Function: number-to-string number
     Convert NUMBER to a string.

 -- Function: string-to-number str
     Parse STR as a number.

 -- Function: string-prefix-p prefix str
     Return true when STR starts with PREFIX.

 -- Function: string-suffix-p suffix str
     Return true when STR ends with SUFFIX.

 -- Function: string-contains-p needle str
     Return true when STR contains NEEDLE.

 -- Function: regexp-quote str
     Escape STR for use as a regular-expression literal.

 -- Function: string-match-spans pattern str [case-sensitive]
     Return match spans for regular-expression PATTERN.

 -- Function: string-match-spans-all pattern str
     Return _all_ match spans (with capture groups) for a global
     regular-expression PATTERN against STR, as a pure query that does
     not mutate editor match state.  Returns ‘(ok t matches)’ on
     success, or ‘(ok nil error details)’ for an invalid regex.

 -- Function: literal-match-spans needle str [case-sensitive]
     Return match spans for literal NEEDLE.

 -- Function: string-flex-spans pattern str [case-sensitive]
     Return spans for flexible ordered-character matching.

 -- Function: string-initialism-spans pattern str [case-sensitive]
     Return spans for initialism matching across word starts.

 -- Function: display-width str
     Return display width used by the current T-Lisp renderer helpers.

 -- Function: truncate-display str width
     Return STR truncated to WIDTH display cells.

7.5 Type Predicates
===================

 -- Function: null expr
     Test if EXPR is nil or empty list.

 -- Function: atom expr
     Test if EXPR is not a list.

 -- Function: numberp expr
     Test if EXPR is a number.

 -- Function: stringp expr
     Test if EXPR is a string.

 -- Function: symbolp expr
     Test if EXPR is a symbol.

 -- Function: listp expr
     Test if EXPR is a list.

 -- Function: functionp expr
     Test if EXPR is a function.

 -- Function: hashmapp expr
     Test if EXPR is a hash map.

 -- Function: nilp expr
     Test if EXPR is nil.

 -- Function: zerop number
     Test if NUMBER is zero.

 -- Function: evenp number
     Test if NUMBER is even.

 -- Function: oddp number
     Test if NUMBER is odd.

7.6 Logical
===========

 -- Function: not expr
     Logical negation.  Returns ‘#t’ if EXPR is falsy.

7.7 I/O
=======

 -- Function: print args...
     Print arguments to stdout.

 -- Function: princ arg
     Print ARG without adding a newline.  Available in the standalone
     runtime profile.

 -- Function: read-line
     Read one line from standard input.  Available in the standalone
     runtime profile.

 -- Function: read-file path
     Read PATH as UTF-8 text.  Available in the standalone runtime
     profile.

 -- Function: write-file path content
     Write CONTENT to PATH.  Available in the standalone runtime
     profile.

 -- Function: file-exists? path
     Return true when PATH exists.  Available in the standalone runtime
     profile.

 -- Function: directory-files path
     Return directory entries for PATH.  Available in the standalone
     runtime profile.

7.8 System
==========

 -- Function: getenv name
     Return the environment variable named NAME, or nil.

 -- Function: current-time
     Return the current Unix timestamp in milliseconds.

 -- Function: exit code
     Exit the standalone CLI with CODE.

 -- Function: shell-command command
     Run COMMAND with the host shell and return stdout.  This primitive
     is opt-in for standalone profile construction and enabled by the
     CLI.

7.9 Hash Maps
=============

 -- Function: hashmap key1 value1 key2 value2...
     Create a hash map from key-value pairs.
          (hashmap "name" "tmax" "version" "0.2")

 -- Function: hashmap-get map key
     Get value for KEY from MAP.  Returns nil if not found.

 -- Function: hashmap-set map key value
     Return new map with KEY set to VALUE (immutable).

 -- Function: hashmap-keys map
     Return list of all keys.

 -- Function: hashmap-values map
     Return list of all values.

 -- Function: hashmap-has-key? map key
     Test if MAP contains KEY.

7.10 Keymaps
============

 -- Function: defkeymap name
     Create and define a new keymap.

 -- Function: keymap-get keymap property
     Get a property from a keymap.

 -- Function: keymap-define-key keymap key command
     Bind KEY to COMMAND in KEYMAP.

 -- Function: keymap-lookup keymap key
     Look up binding for KEY in KEYMAP.

7.11 Variables
==============

 -- Function: setq name value
     Set variable NAME to VALUE in the global environment.
          (setq tab-width 4)

7.12 Callable Helpers
=====================

 -- Function: funcall function args...
     Call FUNCTION with ARGS.

 -- Function: apply function args... list
     Call FUNCTION with positional ARGS followed by the elements of
     LIST.

 -- Function: identity value
     Return VALUE.

 -- Function: symbol-name symbol
     Return the printed name of SYMBOL.


