12 Editor API -- Buffer
***********************

 -- Function: buffer-create name
     Create a new buffer named NAME.

 -- Function: buffer-switch name
     Switch to buffer NAME.

 -- Function: buffer-current
     Return name of current buffer, or nil.

 -- Function: buffer-list
     Return list of all buffer names.

 -- Function: buffer-text
     Return entire buffer content as string.

 -- Function: buffer-line LINENUM
     Return content of line LINENUM.  If omitted, returns current line.

 -- Function: buffer-lines
     Return list of all lines in current buffer.

 -- Function: buffer-line-count
     Return number of lines in current buffer.

 -- Function: buffer-insert text
     Insert TEXT at cursor position and advance cursor.

 -- Function: buffer-delete count
     Delete COUNT characters at cursor.  Returns deleted text.

 -- Function: buffer-filename
     Return filename of current buffer, or nil.

 -- Function: set-buffer-filename path
     Set filename for current buffer to PATH.

 -- Function: buffer-modified-p
     Return ‘#t’ if buffer has unsaved changes.

 -- Function: set-buffer-modified-p flag
     Set modified flag to FLAG.

 -- Function: buffer-get-line-indent lineNum
     Return indentation level (number of spaces) of line LINENUM.

 -- Function: buffer-set-line-indent lineNum column
     Set indentation of line LINENUM to COLUMN spaces.

 -- Function: buffer-previous-non-blank-line lineNum
     Find previous non-blank line number from LINENUM.  Returns -1 if
     none.

 -- Function: buffer-line-matches lineNum pattern
     Test if line LINENUM matches regex PATTERN.

 -- Function: buffer-get-range start-line start-column end-line
          end-column
     Return the text within the given range without modifying the
     buffer.

 -- Function: buffer-delete-range start-line start-column end-line
          end-column
     Delete the text within the given range, move the cursor to the
     range start, and return the deleted text.

 -- Function: buffer-insert-at-position line column text
     Insert TEXT at the given LINE and COLUMN (unlike ‘buffer-insert’,
     this does not use the cursor position) and advance the cursor past
     the inserted text.  Returns the inserted text.

 -- Function: buffer-get-char-at-position line column
     Return the single character at LINE and COLUMN, or nil when out of
     bounds.

 -- Function: buffer-scan-forward-from line column stop-chars max-chars
     Scan right from COLUMN on LINE and return the exclusive end of the
     run of characters not in STOP-CHARS, as ‘(line column truncated)’.
     MAX-CHARS bounds the scan.

 -- Function: buffer-scan-backward-from line column stop-chars max-chars
     Scan left from COLUMN on LINE and return the inclusive start of the
     run of characters not in STOP-CHARS, as ‘(line column truncated)’.
     MAX-CHARS bounds the scan.

 -- Function: buffer-set-read-only flag
     Set the current buffer's read-only state using FLAG (boolean,
     ‘t’/nil, or non-zero number) and return the new boolean state.


