40 Editor API -- Clipboard
**************************

Direct access to the operating-system clipboard.  This is distinct from
the *note Editor API --- Kill Ring::, which is tmax's in-editor deletion
history.

 -- Function: clipboard-available?
     Return ‘#t’ when an OS clipboard tool is available on this
     platform.

 -- Function: clipboard-get
     Return the text currently on the OS clipboard, or ‘""’ when
     unavailable or empty.

 -- Function: clipboard-set text
     Write TEXT to the OS clipboard.  Returns nil on success, or an
     error when no clipboard tool is available.


File: tlisp.info,  Node: Editor API --- Terminal & Viewport,  Next: Editor API --- Browse URL,  Prev: Editor API --- Clipboard,  Up: Top

41 Editor API -- Terminal & Viewport
************************************

 -- Function: terminal-height-get
     Return the terminal height in lines (used for page-size
     calculations).

 -- Function: terminal-width-get
     Return the terminal width in columns (defaults to 80 when
     unavailable).

 -- Function: viewport-top-get
     Return the current viewport top line.

 -- Function: viewport-top-set top
     Set the viewport top line to TOP (clamped to ‘>= 0’) and return the
     new value.

 -- Function: viewport-left-get
     Return the current viewport left column (horizontal scroll).

 -- Function: viewport-left-set left
     Set the viewport left column to LEFT (clamped to ‘>= 0’) and return
     the new value.


File: tlisp.info,  Node: Editor API --- Browse URL,  Next: Testing Framework,  Prev: Editor API --- Terminal & Viewport,  Up: Top

42 Editor API -- Browse URL
***************************

 -- Function: browse-doc-reference reference kind
     Resolve a documentation REFERENCE of KIND (‘"rfc"’ or ‘"spec"’) to
     its canonical file path under ‘docs/rfcs’/‘docs/specs’.  Returns
     ‘(ok t path url)’ on success, or ‘(ok nil error details)’ on
     failure.

 -- Function: browse-git-github-remote
     Walk up from the current buffer's file to find a ‘.git’ directory
     and parse the GitHub remote (origin, upstream, or first match) from
     its config.  Returns ‘(ok t owner repo remote url worktree)’, or
     ‘(ok nil error details)’.


