43 Testing Framework
********************

T-Lisp includes a built-in testing framework for writing and running
tests.

 -- Function: deftest name () body...
     Define a named test.
          (deftest "addition works" ()
            (assert-equal 3 (+ 1 2)))

 -- Function: test-run name
     Run the test named NAME.

 -- Function: test-run-all
     Run all registered tests.  Returns ‘(passed failed total)’.

 -- Function: assert-true value
     Assert that VALUE is truthy.

 -- Function: assert-false value
     Assert that VALUE is falsy.

 -- Function: assert-equal expected actual
     Assert that EXPECTED equals ACTUAL.

 -- Function: assert-not-equal expected actual
     Assert that EXPECTED does not equal ACTUAL.

 -- Function: assert-error form
     Assert that FORM raises an error when evaluated.


